### Subconscious Engine API — manual smoke tests
#
# Usage (VS Code "REST Client" or JetBrains HTTP client):
#   1. Start the engine so the API is listening:  `subconscious engine`
#   2. Open the discovery file it writes to your data dir: `runtime.json`
#      and copy the `port` and `token` values into the variables below.
#   3. Click "Send Request" above each request.
#
# The API binds to loopback only (127.0.0.1) and every endpoint except
# /health requires the bearer token from runtime.json.

@host = 127.0.0.1
@port = 8771
@baseUrl = http://{{host}}:{{port}}/api/v1
@token = PASTE_TOKEN_FROM_runtime.json_HERE


### Health — no auth required. Should return 200 with status/version/node_id.
# @name health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json


### Health should still work even with a bogus token (endpoint is unauthenticated).
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Authorization: Bearer not-a-real-token
Accept: application/json


### List configured models — requires auth. API keys are never returned.
# The one flagged "is_default": true is used when chat.send omits model_id.
# @name listModels
GET {{baseUrl}}/models
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


### List workspaces — requires a valid token. Capture the first workspace uuid.
# @name listWorkspaces
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspaces
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


### Negative check: missing token should return 401.
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspaces
Accept: application/json


### Negative check: wrong token should return 401.
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspaces
Authorization: Bearer wrong-token
Accept: application/json


# Pull the first workspace uuid from the listWorkspaces response above so the
# following requests can reference it without manual copy/paste.
@workspaceUuid = {{listWorkspaces.response.body.$[0].uuid}}


### List threads in a workspace.
# @name listThreads
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspaces/{{workspaceUuid}}/threads
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


### Create a new thread in that workspace.
# @name createThread
POST {{baseUrl}}/threads
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workspace_uuid": "{{workspaceUuid}}",
  "title": "Smoke test thread",
  "description": "Created via api.http"
}


# Reference the thread we just created.
@threadUuid = {{createThread.response.body.uuid}}


### Update the thread (rename + set a model id).
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/threads/{{threadUuid}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Smoke test thread (renamed)",
  "default_model_id": "default"
}


### List messages for the thread (empty until a chat is run over the WebSocket).
GET {{baseUrl}}/threads/{{threadUuid}}/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


### Negative check: unknown workspace uuid should return 404.
GET {{baseUrl}}/workspaces/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/threads
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


### Negative check: unknown thread uuid should return 404.
GET {{baseUrl}}/threads/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/messages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json


### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### WebSocket chat (not runnable from .http — documented for reference)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Connect:  ws://{{host}}:{{port}}/api/v1/events?token={{token}}
#
# Send a chat message. `model_id` is optional — omit it to use the default
# model (the one flagged is_default by GET /models). A supplied-but-unknown
# id returns a chat.error frame.
#
#   {
#     "v": 1,
#     "type": "chat.send",
#     "id": "client-correlation-id",
#     "data": {
#       "thread_uuid": "<thread uuid>",
#       "content": "Hello!",
#       "model_id": "<uuid from GET /models, optional>"
#     }
#   }
#
# Server replies stream back as chat.delta frames, then a final chat.done
# (or chat.error on failure), each echoing the same "id".
